9:["$","h2","h2-3",{"children":"3. Technical Architecture"}]
a:["$","h3","h3-0",{"children":"3.1 Sensor Suite"}]
b:["$","p","p-6",{"children":"Modern L4 vehicles use multiple redundant sensor modalities:"}]
c:["$","p","p-7",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"LIDAR (Light Detection and Ranging)"}],":"]}]
d:["$","ul","ul-2",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Emits laser pulses, measures return time to generate 3D point clouds at 10–20 Hz."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Range: 100–300m; unaffected by ambient lighting."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Key vendors: Velodyne (HDL-64E), Luminar (Iris), Ouster, Innoviz."}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Solid-state LIDAR"}]," (2024–2025): No moving parts; cheaper, more reliable. ADAS-grade units at <$200 (Hesai AT128)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":"Limitation: Degraded in heavy rain, fog, snow."}],"\n"]}]
e:["$","p","p-8",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Cameras"}],":"]}]
f:["$","ul","ul-3",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Primary perception sensor for object recognition, lane detection, traffic sign reading."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Forward-facing (8MP, 200m range), side cameras (120° FOV), rear cameras."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Tesla's vision-only approach (eliminated LIDAR/radar in 2021) remains controversial—relies entirely on neural networks to reconstruct 3D scene from monocular cameras."}],"\n"]}]
10:["$","p","p-9",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Radar"}],":"]}]
11:["$","ul","ul-4",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Measures velocity and range robustly in all weather. Key for ACC (adaptive cruise control)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"4D radar (including height, 2023–2025): Arbe, ZF, Continental. Approaches LIDAR spatial resolution."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Long range: 200m+; short range: 30m wide FOV for cross-traffic detection."}],"\n"]}]
12:["$","p","p-10",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Ultrasonic sensors"}],":"]}]
13:["$","ul","ul-5",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Short-range (<5m), low-cost parking/proximity sensing. Standard on all modern vehicles."}],"\n"]}]
14:["$","p","p-11",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Sensor fusion architecture"}],":"]}]
15:["$","ul","ul-6",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Early fusion"}],": Combine raw sensor data before processing (high bandwidth, challenging synchronization)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Late fusion"}],": Process each sensor independently, merge decisions (modular but loses cross-modal context)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Deep fusion"}],": Process in shared neural network backbone (state-of-the-art for perception accuracy)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Kalman filters and particle filters for state estimation across sensor streams."}],"\n"]}]
16:["$","h3","h3-1",{"children":"3.2 High-Definition (HD) Maps"}]
17:["$","p","p-12",{"children":"AVs require maps with 10–20cm accuracy (vs. 1–5m for consumer GPS navigation):"}]
18:["$","ul","ul-7",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Lane centerlines, boundaries, speed limits, traffic signal positions"}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Built via survey vehicles equipped with LIDAR + cameras"}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Localization"}],": LIDAR scan matching against HD map provides centimeter-level positioning"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":"Key vendors: HERE, TomTom, Mobileye REM (crowdsourced from fleet cameras)"}],"\n",["$","li","li-4",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Challenge"}],": Map freshness—construction zones, road changes can invalidate maps. Crowdsourced update pipelines are critical."]}],"\n"]}]
19:["$","h3","h3-2",{"children":"3.3 Perception Stack"}]
1a:["$","p","p-13",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Object detection and classification"}],":"]}]
1b:["$","ul","ul-8",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Detect and classify: vehicles, pedestrians, cyclists, animals, debris."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"State-of-the-art: Transformer-based multi-modal detectors (BEVFormer, BEV-Fusion) achieving 68+ NDS on nuScenes benchmark (2024)."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Occupancy networks (2023–2025)"}],": Predict a voxel-level occupancy grid of the environment—captures arbitrary obstacles without pre-defined object classes. Tesla Occupancy Networks, Meta's OccFormer."]}],"\n"]}]
1c:["$","p","p-14",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Behavior prediction"}],":"]}]
1d:["$","ul","ul-9",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":"Predict future trajectories of surrounding agents (pedestrians, vehicles) over 3–8 second horizons."}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Models: Wayformer, MTR (Motion Transformer). Benchmark: Waymo Open Motion Dataset competition."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":"Critical for safe merging, intersection navigation, pedestrian crossing scenarios."}],"\n"]}]
1e:["$","h3","h3-3",{"children":"3.4 Planning and Control"}]
1f:["$","p","p-15",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Planning hierarchy"}],":"]}]
20:["$","ol","ol-0",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Route planning"}],": A* / Dijkstra on road network graph (GPS-level, seconds to compute)"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Behavioral planning"}],": Decision-making (lane change, yield, merge) via rule-based + learned models"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Motion planning"}],": Smooth, dynamically feasible trajectory generation (polynomial splines, optimization-based)"]}],"\n",["$","li","li-3",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Trajectory tracking"}],": MPC or PID controllers execute planned trajectory at actuator level"]}],"\n"]}]
21:["$","p","p-16",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Learning-based planning"}]," (emerging 2024–2026):"]}]
22:["$","ul","ul-10",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"End-to-end learning"}],": Single neural network from sensor input to steering/throttle output. Tesla FSD, Wayve GAIA."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":"Advantage: Handles complex unscripted scenarios. Disadvantage: Less interpretable, harder to certify."}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"imitation learning from human demonstrations"}],": Scale of demonstration data (millions of miles) allows learning rare scenarios."]}],"\n"]}]
