46:["$","p","p-24",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"V2V (Vehicle-to-Vehicle)"}],": Direct 5.9 GHz communication; share position, speed, heading to prevent intersection collisions. Range: 300–500m through obstacles."]}]
47:["$","p","p-25",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Technologies"}],":"]}]
48:["$","ul","ul-21",{"children":["\n",["$","li","li-0",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"DSRC (Dedicated Short-Range Communications)"}],": IEEE 802.11p standard; proven, deployed. USDOT invested $575M in infrastructure (2021–2024)."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-1",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"C-V2X (Cellular V2X)"}],": 4G/5G LTE sidelink; higher bandwidth, network-coordinated. Qualcomm, Ericsson backing."]}],"\n",["$","li","li-2",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"5G NR-V2X"}],": Ultra-reliable low-latency communication (<1ms) for cooperative driving at highway speeds."]}],"\n"]}]
49:["$","p","p-26",{"children":"V2X is increasingly recognized as complementary to onboard sensing—reducing edge cases, enabling cooperative perception (multiple vehicles sharing sensor data for a shared world model)."}]
4a:["$","hr","hr-7",{}]
4b:["$","h2","h2-7",{"children":"7. Key Challenges"}]
4c:["$","p","p-27",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Edge cases"}],": Long-tail scenarios (unusual vehicle types, novel road conditions, unexpected pedestrian behavior) are rare in training data but critical for safety. Statistical confidence requires billions of miles."]}]
4d:["$","p","p-28",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Sensor limitations in adverse weather"}],": Heavy rain, snow, and fog degrade LIDAR and camera performance. Solutions: heated LIDAR housings, radar-first fusion, HD map fallback."]}]
4e:["$","p","p-29",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Regulation fragmentation"}],": 50 US state frameworks + international divergence increases development cost and deployment complexity. Unified federal framework remains pending."]}]
4f:["$","p","p-30",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Public trust and acceptance"}],": After high-profile incidents (Cruise 2023), public trust erodes faster than it builds. Transparent safety reporting (Waymo's approach) is critical."]}]
50:["$","p","p-31",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Cybersecurity"}],": Connected AVs are attack surfaces. Demonstrated attacks include spoofing GPS, injecting adversarial stop signs into camera feeds, exploiting OTA update mechanisms."]}]
51:["$","p","p-32",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"Cost of sensor hardware"}],": LIDAR costs dropped from $75,000 (Velodyne HDL-64E, 2010) to <$500 (solid-state, 2025)—enabling commercial viability. Compute costs (NX-class Orin, $500–1000/vehicle) also declining."]}]
52:["$","hr","hr-8",{}]
53:["$","h2","h2-8",{"children":"8. Timeline and Outlook"}]
54:["$","table","table-2",{"children":[["$","thead","thead-0",{"children":["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","th","th-0",{"children":"Milestone"}],["$","th","th-1",{"children":"Status (May 2026)"}]]}]}],["$","tbody","tbody-0",{"children":[["$","tr","tr-0",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"L4 robotaxis in geofenced urban areas"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"✅ Deployed (Waymo, Baidu)"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-1",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"L3 on highways (certified)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"✅ Mercedes Drive Pilot"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-2",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"L4 autonomous trucking commercial"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"✅ Aurora (Texas freight, 2024)"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-3",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"L4 in adverse weather without HD maps"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"🔄 In research; 2028–2031 estimated"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-4",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"L5 full automation (all conditions)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"❌ No clear timeline; research challenge"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-5",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Autonomous trucking at scale (1000+ units)"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"🔄 2027–2030 projected"}]]}],["$","tr","tr-6",{"children":[["$","td","td-0",{"children":"Consumer-purchasable L4 vehicles"}],["$","td","td-1",{"children":"🔄 2028–2032 (regulatory + cost dependent)"}]]}]]}]]}]
55:["$","p","p-33",{"children":[["$","strong","strong-0",{"children":"McKinsey projection"}]," [2023]: L4+ commercialization at scale by 2030–2035, contingent on regulatory clarity and sensor cost reduction continuing."]}]
